            <div type="edition"><!-- transcription goes here -->
                <ab>
                    <lb n="1"/><persName><gap reason="lost" atLeast="1" atMost="3" unit="character"/>σίου</persName> θ<supplied reason="lost" cert="low">υγά</supplied>
                    <lb n="2" break="no"/>τηρ ἔζ<supplied reason="lost" cert="high">ησεν</supplied><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>
                    <lb n="3"/><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> ἔτη <num value="3"><hi rend="supraline">Γ</hi></num>, μῆν<supplied reason="lost" cert="high">ας <num atLeast="1"><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/></num></supplied>                
                </ab>
            </div>
             
            <div type="commentary"><!-- notes go here -->
            <p>completion of the verb in line 3 is expected before the age of the deceased; thus
                    there are only approximately 3 characters missing on the right side of the text.
                    It is possible that little is missing from the left as well thus yeilding the
                    reconstruction of θυγάτηρ over the line break. This then would limit the
                    reconstruction of the name ending in -σιου to only a few additional letters. One
                    would however, except the name of the father after the noun to complete the
                    nomenclature.</p></div>
            
